bug.short_desc: Problem with grid layout: a label is layoutet outside its parent

long_desc.thetext:
Hello Uwe, I tried to reproduce the bug but failed. Copied your code to the playground (current, trunk and r25184) using my mac. I tried Chrome 12 (dev), Firefox 3.6 and Firefox 4 but could not reproduce the issue. Something seems to be different in your setup. Could you maybe retest the supplied example code in the devel version of the playground [1] and give me some more details about your setup? Maybe its browser / OS dependent? Would be good if you could drop me a quick note that i can get it into the trunk before the code freeze for 1.4 (Thursday). Thanks!
[1] http://demo.qooxdoo.org/devel/playground/#

I still have the problem with the new version of the playground. I get this problem with several browsers (Firefox 4, Safari, Opera). This problem should be reproducible by opening the following URL with any of these browsers: http://tinyurl.com/4t2wk32 Then you should see a text that is cut of half.

(In reply to comment #3) > I still have the problem with the new version of the playground. > I get this problem with several browsers (Firefox 4, Safari, Opera). > This problem should be reproducible by opening the following URL with any of > these browsers: > http://tinyurl.com/4t2wk32 > Then you should see a text that is cut of half.
I can confirm that in Chrome 8.0.552.215 on Linux, using the above playground link, I see only half of the text.
Derrell
Thats really a strange thing, its working on my mac but not on linux and windows. Great!
